solid oxide fuel cells with atomic layer deposited platinum catalyst ecs transactions 25 855 2009 solid oxide fuel cells with atomic layer deposited platinum catalyst ecs transactions 25 855 2009 cheng chieh chao fritz b prinz abstract platinum can serve as a catalyst for enhancing the kinetics of hydrogen oxidation reactions hor and oxygen reduction reactions orr in fuel cell operations in a previous study we fabricated a solid oxide fuel cell sofc with an atomic layer deposited ald yttria stabilized zirconia ysz electrolyte and sputtered porous platinum electrodes to improve the bonding between the electrolyte and the electrodes we deposited a one nanometer platinum layer in situ on top of the electrolyte an 80 improvement in maximum power density was observed at 450 c due to the reduction of activation losses
